&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Ravenchief was certain his team could handle one Predecon, and continued
&gt; searching.  Using energon readings, he noted the location of the other bot
&gt; on his scanner.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Here kitty kitty kitty&quot; he called out to the wounded lion.

&lt;NEW&gt;

The KITTY as he was (not) so affectionately called just stopped as
RAVENCHIEF had finally located him, it had just stepped out from one
of the buildings. The armor on his back flexing slightly as a the
hackles on a real cat might do and he just looked for a moment.

A simple scan was still showing energon leacking from his systems, but
a closer view showed many wounds, some of them healing but others of
them much fresher. It looked as if he had been through several
battles, not all of them he had won. In fact, although his armor
looked more or less intact, internal scanning showed large amounts of
still unhealed damage that his systems were still struggling to keep
running.

*ROoaar . . cough cough*

The lion tried to roar, but the decibel count was significantly less
than before, sounding more like a bull horn than the ear and glass
shattering blast he had done some time earlier. And this one actually
faded into something like a mechanical cough.

With a strange sort of dignity the cat turned away and tried to walk
away, although the movement was no longer as fast or as strong as it
once was.

It was trying to head back into one of the other buildings.

